<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880805-0035 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Douglas andamp; Lomason Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DOUG </CO><TEXT>   Douglas andamp; Lomason Co., Farmington Hills, Mich., said it expects to post a third-quarter loss, compared with year-earlier profit of $240,800, or seven cents a share.    The auto-parts supplier cited slow summer business because of vacation shutdowns at the major auto makers, particularly Ford Motor Co. The company also said it anticipates a further drain from start-up costs at two new plants. </TEXT></DOC>